               <p>HENRY BOLTON. I am a <rs id="t18340703-143-viclabel792" type="occupation">gardener</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340703-143-victim881 t18340703-143-viclabel792"></join>, and lodge with Mary Ann Williams, in <placeName id="t18340703-143-crimeloc793">Bull-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340703-143-crimeloc793" type="placeName" value="Bull-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340703-143-crimeloc793" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340703-143-off789 t18340703-143-crimeloc793"></join>, in the parish of Fulham. The prisoner is a <rs id="t18340703-143-deflabel794" type="occupation">labouring gardener</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340703-143-defend880 t18340703-143-deflabel794"></join>, and lodged in the same house, on and off, for two years - he had not given up his lodging on Tuesday, the 20th of May - I went out that afternoon, between three and four o'clock, and left nobody in the house - I left it quite secure and fast - the front door bolted - the back door has no latch, but could only be opened by means of a stick, which those who were accus<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183407030063"></xptr>tomed to the house knew of, but a stranger could not get in - I left my trowsers and all this property locked up in my box - one waistcoat hung on the balustrade - there was in my box 2l. in silver and 30s. in copper - the value of the property lost is 5l. 1s. 6d. at a very moderate rate - that is rather under the mark - my box was locked; I had the key in my pocket - I returned at ten o'clock at night - my landlady came home at that time - she went in first at the back door - I found my box broken open, and the articles and money stated taken away - I found this bent poker in the room - there were marks on the box which corresponded with the poker - the prisoner did not return home that night - I went next morning and found him asleep at the Three Crowns, Chelsea, and gave him in charge - a bundle was under another man's head - the prisoner was searched directly - he claimed the bundle as being his - I found in his pocket two knives, which were mine, and 1s. 1d.; the knives had been in my box, the bundle contained my waistcoat and trowsers.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340703-143-person883">
                  MOSES 
                  MOORE
               <interp inst="t18340703-143-person883" type="surname" value="MOORE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340703-143-person883" type="given" value="MOSES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340703-143-person883" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I went into the Three Crowns public-house, at Chelsea: I found the prisoner there with a bundle - I fell asleep on the bundle - Bolton came in, and the prisoner said the bundle was his.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340703-143-person884">
                  JANE 
                  RICKMAN
               <interp inst="t18340703-143-person884" type="surname" value="RICKMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340703-143-person884" type="given" value="JANE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340703-143-person884" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in the neighbourhood. On the Tuesday night in question I saw the prisoner near the prosecutor's house about a quarter before five o'clock - he came out of the back yard with a bundle tied in a blue handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340703-143-person885">
                  SAMUEL 
                  GUNN
               <interp inst="t18340703-143-person885" type="surname" value="GUNN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340703-143-person885" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340703-143-person885" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a policeman. I was sent for - I searched the prisoner at the station-house, and found this knife in his pocket - he told me he had the property given to him, and afterwards he said he found it in the back yard of the premises where he lodged.</p>
